        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Farnborough Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Wednesday</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I have just received a Circular from Palæont. Soc. to say there will be a Council on next Monday afternoon: I shall attend it; it w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be an immense saving of time &amp; trouble, if you could <hi rend="doubleUnderline">make an effort</hi> &amp; let me have <hi rend="doubleUnderline">all</hi> the <hi rend="doubleUnderline">rough arranged by</hi> <hi rend="doubleUnderline">2</hi> <hi rend="doubleUnderline">oclock</hi> on <hi rend="doubleUnderline">Monday</hi> at the <hi rend="underline">Geological</hi> <hi rend="underline">Soc</hi> <hi rend="underline">Somerset</hi> H:—— Let me earnestly beg you to put your shoulder to the wheel &amp; get the job done</p>
<p>Yours vy truly | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.4 <hi rend="bold">2</hi>] <hi rend="italic">altered from</hi> ‘<hi rend="bold">3</hi>’</note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Dated on the basis that this letter precedes <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1353.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. S. Bowerbank, 10 September [1850]</ref>, in which it is made apparent that CD did attend the council meeting of the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3646.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Palaeontographical Society</ref> mentioned in the letter.</note>
        </div>        
            
